hiawatha (12.0-4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * debian/hiawatha.service: switch ExecStartPre from hiawatha -k to
    wigwam -q, the purpose-built config validator.
  * debian/hiawatha.service: add config validation to ExecReload — run
    wigwam -q before sending HUP so a broken config cannot take down a
    running instance on reload. Shell wrapper required as systemd ExecReload
    does not support conditional chaining natively; $MAINPID is expanded by
    systemd before the string is passed to sh.
  * debian/hiawatha.init: switch do_start() config check from hiawatha -k
    to wigwam -q; remove stdout/stderr suppression so syntax errors are
    visible rather than silently swallowed.
  * debian/hiawatha.init: add wigwam -q to do_reload() so a bad config
    cannot cause a live instance to be signalled into an undefined state.
  * debian/hiawatha.init: add explicit wigwam -q pre-flight to the restart
    case before do_stop(), ensuring config is verified while the server is
    still running. do_start() retains its own check as a safety net.

 -- Chris Wadge <cwadge@tuxhelp.org>  Fri, 03 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

hiawatha (12.0-3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add debian/hiawatha.init — LSB-compliant SysV init script for
    compatibility with sysvinit and OpenRC-based systems (Devuan, etc.).
    dh_installinit handles permissions and update-rc.d integration
    automatically via debhelper compat 13.

 -- Chris Wadge <cwadge@tuxhelp.org>  Fri, 04 Apr 2026 20:00:00 +0000

hiawatha (12.0-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add debian/hiawatha.service — upstream CMakeLists.txt does not install
    a systemd unit file; provide one as a packaging overlay so that the
    service can be managed via systemctl after installation.

 -- Chris Wadge <cwadge@tuxhelp.org>  Fri, 04 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000

